Reference-contexts: 1. Introduction This document describes SCRAPI, a simple ``Bare Bones'' API for RSVP <ref> [1] </ref>. The goal of this API is produce an interface which simplifies the augmentation of applications with RSVP support. The main features of SCRAPI are: Allow the addition of RSVP support to applications by adding a few lines of code.
Reference: [2] <author> Braden, R., Hoffman, D., </author> <title> RAPI -- An RSVP Application Programming Interface Version 5, </title> <booktitle> Work In Progress, </booktitle> <month> November </month> <year> 1997. </year>
Reference-contexts: Provide a portable interface which can be used with any vendor's RAPI implementation. Avoid the introduction of RSVP specific data types and definitions. Support IPv4 and IPv6 in a transparent manner. SCRAPI is layered on top of RAPI <ref> [2] </ref>, an existing RSVP API, to provide portability across vendor implementations. Currently, SCRAPI has been tested only with the ISI implementation of RAPI.
