Reference-contexts: Lindell Expiration: February 1999 [Page 2] INTERNET-DRAFT SCRAPI v.1 July 1998 2. Functional Description Applications which use SCRAPI get a simplied service model. The average bandwidth specified by the sender is currently translated into the integrated services controlled load [4] or guaranteed service <ref> [3] </ref> with the given average bandwidth. The peak bandwidth and token bucket depth are set to twice the average bandwidth. Minimum policed unit and maximum packet size are set to 64 bytes and the largest MTU of all IP interfaces on the host.

